  facet_wrap(~ week_day) +
  geom_density(aes(fill = client), color = NA, alpha = .33, position = position_stack())

In my opinion, the fifth graph is most interesting because it indicates not only when bicycle rentals are at its highest, but also shows which group of clients make up the majority of bicycle rentals at any given time of day.

6

Trips %>% 
  mutate(time_of_day = 
lubridate::hour(sdate) + lubridate::minute(sdate) / 60, week_day = ifelse(lubridate::wday(sdate) %in% c(6,7),"weekend","weekday")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = time_of_day)) +
  facet_wrap(~ week_day) +
  geom_density(aes(fill = client), color = NA, alpha = .33, position = position_stack())

It is best to facet the way we did so that the Weekday and Weekend facets correctly correspond to the time of day (it is much clearer to interpret time of day this way). Doing the other faceting would be confusing when interpreting the x-axis.

Trip Distance

1

Left <-
  Stations %>%
  select(name,lat,long) %>%
  dplyr::rename(sstation = name)

Right <-
  Stations %>%
  select(name,lat,long) %>%
  dplyr::rename(estation = name, lat2 = lat, long2 = long)

Stations <-
  Left %>%
  merge(Right,all=TRUE)
source("http://tiny.cc/dcf/haversine.R")

2

Stations <-
  Stations %>%
  mutate(dist = haversine(lat, long, lat2, long2))

Distances <-
  Stations %>%
  select(sstation,estation,dist)

3

Trips <-
  Trips %>%
  left_join(Distances)

Distribution of Distances

1

Trips %>%
  mutate(week_day = ifelse(lubridate::wday(sdate) %in% c(6,7),"weekend","weekday")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = dist)) + 
  geom_density() + 
  facet_grid(client ~ week_day)

2

Trips %>%
  mutate(week_day = ifelse(lubridate::wday(sdate) %in% c(6,7),"weekend","weekday"), hour = lubridate::hour(sdate)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = hour, y = dist)) + 
  ylim(0,5) +
  geom_violin(aes(group = hour)) +
  stat_smooth() +
  facet_grid(client ~ week_day)

Trips %>%
  mutate(week_day = ifelse(lubridate::wday(sdate) %in% c(6,7),"weekend","weekday"), hour = lubridate::hour(sdate)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = hour, y = dist)) + 
  geom_boxplot(aes(group = hour, ymin = 0, ymax = 5), outlier.size = 1, fill = "grey") +
  stat_smooth() +
  ylim(0,5) +
  facet_grid(client ~ week_day)
